text.section:
The Commission shall:
publish annually in at least one newspaper in Montgomery County and one newspaper in Prince George's County a copy of the current financial statement of the Commission;
employ a certified public accountant licensed to practice in the State to audit the books and accounts of the Commission;
keep available for public inspection during business hours at its principal office the annual audit and current financial statement; and
file annually with the county executives and county councils of Montgomery County and Prince George's County, and the Montgomery County and Prince George's County Senate and House delegations to the Maryland General Assembly a certified copy of the annual audit and current financial statement.
